 are at least two orders of\nmagnitude weaker than the cosmic microwave background (CMB) fluctuations as\nmeasured in terms of the angular temperature power spectrum. A residual signal\nabove the noise level is present in the multipole range $\\ell<20$, most notably\nat 30 GHz, and is likely caused by residual Galactic straylight contamination.\nCurrent analysis aims to further reduce the level of spurious signals in the\ndata and to improve the systematic effects modelling, in particular with\nrespect to straylight and calibration uncertainties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Mar 2013 20:10:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Mar 2013 15:37:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Jan 2014 14:32:47 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 27 Mar 2014 12:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-29"}
