ments,\n  - masses of series following $\\beta^{+}$ or $\\beta^{-}$ disintegrations,\n  - one and two nucleon separation energies,\n  - half-lives of some isotopes,\n  - the four radioactive family periods.\n  Finally, it is shown that the lepton, hadron, and boson masses can be\npresented in the same frame. This is also partially true for the coupling\nconstants.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Mar 2013 11:21:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-03-22"}
